\n|\nWhen everybody contributes a change to what he or she notices, it is then we will change our world.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nThink good for yourself ,good will follow you.when you think good for others ,happiness will follow you and when happiness follows you, people will follow you.\n\n- irrfan\n|\nLeave fears aside, clean tears away! Tell God 'here I am, use me!' and he'll give you the assignments that will make your life a fulfilled one. Now dress up to work!\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, The Great Hand Book of Quotes\n|\nYes, the brutalities of progress are called revolutions. When they are over, this is recognised: that the human race has been harshly treated, but that it has advanced.\n\n- Victor Hugo, Les Misérables\n|\nSince living is believing, no one can be completely lacking in faith.\n\n- Kentetsu Takamori, Unlocking Tannisho: Shinran's Words on the Pure Land Path\n|\nTo see time and life correctly, you must realize that whenever you waste a second, you are wasting life.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nCome with me,' Mom says.To the library. Books and summertimego together.\n\n- Lisa Schroeder, I Heart You, You Haunt Me\n|\nThe baby batScreamed out in fright,'Turn on the dark,I'm afraid of the light.\n\n- Shel\n|\nOccupy your thoughts with purpose and you will be so busy pursuing a meaningful future there will be no time for doubt, chaos and disappointment.\n\n- Carlos Wallace, The Other 99 T.Y.M.E.S: Train Your Mind to Enjoy Serenity\n|\nYou want a great life? Well, greatness is on the other side of that fu**ing wall... don't just go over it, go through it! What are you waiting for?\n\n- Steve\n|\nThe first time I read an excellent book, it is to me just as if I had gained a new friend. When I read a book over I have perused before, it resembles the meeting with an old one.\n\n- Oliver Goldsmith, The Citizen of the World, Or, Letters from a Chinese Philosopher, Residing in London, to His Friends in the Country, by Dr. Goldsmith\n|\nGrowth in love comes from a place of absence, where the imagination is left to it’s own devices and creates you to be much more then reality would ever allow.\n\n- Coco\n|\nWhen I die, I plan to be laughing hysterically.\n\n- Minari Endou, Dazzle, Volume 02\n|\nSo it is that a writer writes many books. In each book, he intended several urgent and vivid points, many of which he sacrificed as the book's form hardened.\n\n- Annie Dillard, The Writing Life\n|\nAnd wonder, dread and warhave lingered in that landwhere loss and love in turnhave held the upper hand.\n\n- Simon Armitage, Sir Gawain and the Green Knight\n|\nWith Cosmic Ordering, the best days of your life are always ahead of you.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering Guide\n|\nNo matter how worldly I became, there was always that one part of me that never forgot where I came from and how simple life was there.\n\n- Carlos Wallace, The Other 99 T.Y.M.E.S: Train Your Mind to Enjoy Serenity\n|\nIf a book is well written, I always find it too short.\n\n- Jane Austen, Sense and Sensibility\n|\nSometimes, however, there is more than hope.Sometimes there is reason.\n\n- Elizabeth Haydon, The Assassin King\n|\nEven in your pains, troubles or difficulties, create unforgettable memories by putting a smile on the faces of others'.\n\n- WISDOM\n|\nIt is common to represent a title, but inspiring to represent a purpose.\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nWhen life asks you a question, you learn. When you ask a question from life, you cry.\n\n- Rajesh\n|\nIf nobody else will give you a platform, build your own!\n\n- Suzette\n|\nA writer must be fearless. A writer has to be like a clawed animal.'-The Carrie Diaries pg. 337\n\n- Candace\n|\nObserve the things you are instintively attracted to, they are often linked to your purpose and path in 